Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.core

Class GappedLexeme

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.AbstractLexeme
      • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.GappedLexeme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Lexeme

    public class GappedLexeme
extends AbstractLexeme
    A representation of a lexical unit with non-contiguous parts. This is the abstract analog of GappedMultiWord.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu

        Parameters:

        primaryIndex - index of the primary unit

      • GappedLexeme

        public GappedLexeme​(nu.xom.Element el)
        Creates a GappedLexeme from an XML element. The XML element is expected to have multiple children named Part, each of which corresponds to a contiguous lexeme. The primary Part should have the primary attribute set to true.
        Parameters:
        el - the Element that contains GappedLexeme elements
